{"lemma":"حِصْنُ","slug":"حِصْنُ","root":"ح.ص.ن","root_slug":"ح-ص-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ص-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8267","n8271"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%B5%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stronghold, fortress, entrenchment","tags":["also","figuratively"],"examples":[{"text":"لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللهُ حِصْنِي فَمَنْ دَخَلَ حِصْنَي أَمِنَ مِنْ عَذَابِي","english":"\"There is no god but God\" is my fortress and whomever enters my fortress is saved from my torture (hadith)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"armor or weapons"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be inaccessible, to be unattainable, to be fortified (of a fortress or similar location)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be continent, to be chaste, to keep decor (by keeping in husbandly home or unapproached)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَصُنَ (ḥaṣuna, “to be continent, to be chaste, to keep decor”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to render inaccessible, to make unattainable"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to immunize, to vaccinate (that is, to make unattainable for pathogens)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حِصَان (ḥiṣān)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic חִצְנַא / ܚܶܨܢܳܐ (ḥeṣnā, “stronghold, fortress”), assimilating the laryngeal from earlier 𐡇𐡎𐡍𐡀 / ܚܶܣܢܳܐ (ḥesnā, “stronghold, fortress”), also חוּסנַא / ܚܽܘܣܢܳܐ (ḥusnā), already attested in Old Aramaic 𐤇𐤎𐤍𐤀 (ḥsnʾ), deriving from a well-used root ח־ס־ן ܚ ܣ ܢ, which would be cognate to the Arabic root خ ش ن (ḵ š n) related to roughness, or perhaps ح س ن (ḥ s n) related to goodliness, comeliness, if one relates pulchritude with brawn, and fortresses with exaltedness of appearance. This ascription of Aramaic origin is corroborated by the consideration that fortresses are not to be sought in the original place of the Arabic language, and in conformity with this, most other terms for fortresses, castles, and towers are borrowed, بُرْج (burj), قَصْر (qaṣr), بَلَاط (balāṭ), مِجْدَل (mijdal), صَرْح (ṣarḥ), مِحْرَاب (miḥrāb), صَوْمَعَة (ṣawmaʕa), سَرَاي (sarāy), إِيوَان (ʔīwān), قَشْلَة (qašla).\nThe root’s other formations, containing meanings related to inaccessibility, protection, strength, are denominal from the word for the fortress, حِصْن (ḥiṣn)\nThough the root ح ص ن (ḥ ṣ n) contains حِصَان (ḥiṣān, “horse, stallion, stud”), not even this is a strong contender for a native origin in this root, since this word for a stud or stallion, of high register, could have been invented easily in folk poetry from the idea of strength a fortress is connected to, which is supported by the fact that horses are not to be sought in Arabia either, and the other word فَرَس (faras) has also been picked up.\n\nAfter the root ح ص ن (ḥ ṣ n).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ħisˤn/","/ħi.sˤin/","[ħɪ.sˤɪn]","/ħu.sˤun/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8267","headword_ar":"حَصُنَ","root":"HSn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnapN","text_ar":"حَصَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, TA,) said of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSon","text_ar":"حِصْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or fortress], (S,) or of a place, (Mgh, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manuEa","text_ar":"مَنُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [for which the CK erroneously substitutes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamanaEa","text_ar":"وَمَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kakaruma","text_ar":"كَكَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though the verb were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSuna","text_ar":"حَصُنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSana","text_ar":"حَصَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K, TA,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maniyE","text_ar":"مَنِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inaccessible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapproachable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult of access"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, unattainable, by reason of its height;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was fortified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protected against attack, so that one could not gain access to what was within it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSunato","text_ar":"حَصُنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSonN","text_ar":"حُصْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSonN","text_ar":"حَصْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSonN","text_ar":"حِصْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSaAnapN","text_ar":"حَصَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * Msb, * TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoSanato","text_ar":"اَحْصَنَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoSaAnN","text_ar":"اـِحْصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHS~nt","text_ar":"تحصّنت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) said of a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, continent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she abstained from what was not lawful nor decorous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaf~ato","text_ar":"عَفَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, married;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she had a husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSanato","text_ar":"حَصَنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoSinato","text_ar":"اُحْصِنَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 101, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSunato","text_ar":"حَصُنَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is likewise mentioned in this sense:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoSanato","text_ar":"اَحْصَنَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, pregnant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as though pregnancy protected her from a man's going in to her. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSanahu","text_ar":"حَصَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSonN","text_ar":"حَصْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He preserved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarded, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in places inaccessible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapproachable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult of access, as in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSon","text_ar":"حِصْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortress"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also 2 and 4.]"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n8271","headword_ar":"حِصْنٌ","root":"HSn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fortress; a fort; a fortified place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of which the interior is inaccessible;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place that is fortified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protected against attack, so that one cannot gain access to what is within it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place that is unattainable, by reason of its height;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fortified city:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSuwnN","text_ar":"حُصُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSanapN","text_ar":"حِصَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoSaAnN","text_ar":"اَحْصَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlHiSoni","text_ar":"اَبُو الحِصْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlHuSayni","text_ar":"اَبُو الحُصَينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. [Hence, also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolu AlEarabi HuSuwnuhaA *ukuruhaA waA_inaAvuhaA","text_ar":"خَيْلُ العَرَبِ حُصُونُهَا ذُكُرُهَا وَاـِنَاثُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horses of the Arabs are their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSuwn","text_ar":"حُصُون"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the males thereof and the females thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) A man said to 'Abd-Allah Ibn-El-Hasan, “ My father has left the third of his property for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuSuwn","text_ar":"حُصُون"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” and he replied “ Buy thou horses: ” so in the A: in the M, “ Buy thou therewith horses, and mount [men] on them [to fight] in the cause of God. ” (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arms."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a yaHomilu HiSonFA","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ يَحْمِلُ حِصْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came bearing arms."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new moon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moon when it is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hilaAl","text_ar":"هِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhalaAku","text_ar":"الهَلَاكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhilaAlu","text_ar":"الهِلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K"]}]}}